1211.content:
"Hey, (y/n)," Sam said one day, walking into the kitchen one day where you stood, cooking something. You jumped, not expecting to hear his voice, and accidentally knocked the pan to the floor. You groaned loudly, stooping down to grab the handle and pick it back up.

"Dang it, Sam," you growled, "what's the matter with you?"

"All I said was hey."

"Well you scared me and ruined my breakfast!" You tossed the pan into the sink and he smirked at you.

"Someone's crabby."

"I am not crabby." He took a step towards you.

"You're a little crabby." You glared at him. "And it kinda seems like you need to cheer up."

"It kinda seems like you need to go away." You turned back to the stove and turned the burner off, caught off guard when you suddenly felt...

122.content: Why is he tickling you?
122.title: Dean

1221.content:
"Hey...who ate my pie?"

Your stomach dropped when you heard Dean say this from the kitchen. You'd eaten it a couple hours before and had hoped he wouldn't notice. He walked into the bunker library where you sat, trying to look as innocent as possible. You looked up at him.

"Hi."

"Did you eat my pie?" he asked and you tried to hide the blush from your cheeks. He noticed the change in your skin's color and glared at you. "You did, didn't you?"

"N-no," you said, lowering your head so your hair would fall in front of your face and hide it. He walked to the table, closed the book your were reading and grabbed your chin. He turned your head so you were facing him.

"Don't lie to me."

"I'm not lying," you said, standing up from your chair and moving away from him. He followed you as you tried to walk to the doorway. He grabbed your shoulder and turned you back around to face him. He quickly leaned in and breathed in.

"You smell like apples." You couldn't hide your guilty smile now. He leaned in closer and said, "do you know what happens to people who steal my pie?"

"N-no...what?"

All of a sudden, Dean...
1221.title: You ate his pie

1222.content:
"One, two, three, I win." You lay on the mat in the bunker's garage, panting as Dean got off you and sat back on his knees. You looked up at him with sweat on your forehead.

"This isn't fair."

"How's it not fair?"

"You're stronger than me!"

"That's why we're doing this," he said, "to toughen you up."

"Well, I don't want to do this anymore."

You stood up and he did too, blocking you from leaving. You glared at him.

"Come on, one more round."

"NoooOOOooo," you groaned, "I'm tired."

"Please? Just one?" You sighed.

"Fine. One." Dean grinned.

"Awesome." You got in your stance and he got in his, holding each other's shoulders. He counted to three and you were on the floor in no time. You grunted as your body hit the mat and he pinned your arms above your head.

"Okay, you win...AGAIN. Now, I'm really done." You tried to get up but he held you there. "Dean, get off."

"You haven't tapped out yet."

"How am I supposed to tap out with you holding my wrists?"

"Let me give you some incentive to try and get free..."

1222.title: You're wrestling

123.content: Why is he tickling you?
123.title: Castiel

1231.content:
The ruffle of feathers caught your attention immediately. You looked over at Castiel as you lay in bed, reading a book.

"Hello, (y/n)."

"Hey." You set your book down. "What's going on?"

"I just came to ask you a question."

"Okay...what is it?" you asked, sitting up.

"What is tickling?" You stared at him.

"Umm...it's when you touch someone somewhere and they laugh."

"Touch them where?"

"It depends."

"Depends on what?"

"Where they're ticklish!"

"Where are people usually ticklish?" You didn't answer, instead you went back to lying down and reading your book. "(Y/n)?"

"What?"

"Where are--"

"I don't know, sides...belly...armpits, feet, neck. Everywhere, like Dean. I don't know."

All of a sudden, he was beside your bed and you looked over at him.

"Do you mind if I test it out on you?"

"Yeah. I don't like being tickled."

"Why not?"

"Because I don't."

"Is it unpleasant?"

"For some people."

"Please, (y/n)? I will stop when you say." You lowered your book again and sighed.

"Fine. But you better stop."

"I will." He climbed on the bed and sat on your waist. "Where should I tickle first?"

"I'm not choosing." He observed your body and then...
1231.title: He's curious
